explanation: The solution iteratively calculates the bitwise OR of the result with itself right-shifted by 1, effectively filling in all bits up to the desired length. The final result is incremented to ensure it's greater than the previous element. This approach leverages bitwise operations for efficiency and has a logarithmic time complexity due to the iterative nature of the bit filling process.

